&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Our mission&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;bub-content-body&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Constructor’s mission is to enable all educational organisations to provide high-quality digital education to 10x people with 10x efficiency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With strong expertise in machine intelligence and data science, Constructor’s all-in-one platform for education and research addresses today’s pressing educational challenges: access inequality, tech clutter, and low engagement of students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please send your resume in English only.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Brief Job Description:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Owns the end-to-end data analytics lifecycle, from defining measurement frameworks and surfacing insights to supporting product and model decisions. The role works closely with engineering, product, and ML teams, builds and maintains data pipelines and dashboards, and helps shape the analytical foundation of the AI software development project. Requires 3+ years of data analytics experience, with a track record of influencing product outcomes in a fast-moving technical environment.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Mission:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Turn raw product, behavioural, and model data into clear, trustworthy insight that helps the team make better decisions, faster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Education:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or higher in Statistics, Computer Science, Engineering, Economics, or a related quantitative field — or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define measurement frameworks and metrics with product and engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain data pipelines, dashboards, and reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse product, behavioural, and model data to surface actionable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support experiment design and A/B test analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure data quality and consistency across sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years’ experience in data analytics or a similar quantitative role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong SQL and proficiency in Python or R for analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building dashboards (e.g.&amp;nbsp;Tableau, Power BI, Looker, or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid grasp of statistics and experiment design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear communication of findings to technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Nice to Have (Not Obligatory):&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud data warehouses (BigQuery, Snowflake, Redshift).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with ML workflows and model evaluation metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with GitLab for versioning analysis code and pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to EdTech or AI products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;199&quot; data-end=&quot;1027&quot;&gt;💻 Choice of work equipment (e.g., laptop, monitor, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;199&quot; data-end=&quot;1027&quot;&gt;🇬🇧 English classes (iTalki – $130 monthly)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;199&quot; data-end=&quot;1027&quot;&gt;⏰ Flexible schedule (we usually work between 09:00/10:00 and 18:00/19:00 CET or EET)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;199&quot; data-end=&quot;1027&quot;&gt;👶 Newborn bonus (€500 per child)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;199&quot; data-end=&quot;1027&quot;&gt;🧠 Patent remuneration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;199&quot; data-end=&quot;1027&quot;&gt;🌴 Pai

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Our mission&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;bub-content-body&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Constructor’s mission is to enable all educational organisations to provide high-quality digital education to 10x people with 10x efficiency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With strong expertise in machine intelligence and data science, Constructor’s all-in-one platform for education and research addresses today’s pressing educational challenges: access inequality, tech clutter, and low engagement of students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please send your resume in English only.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interns are NOT eligible for equipment and other benefits as the position is temporary.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With this internship, the Frontend Engineering Intern will get full integration into the frontend development team, and he will try a full development cycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Duties &amp;amp; Responsibilities:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand and translate project requirements into responsive and engaging user interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain frontend components using modern web technologies such as HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript (ES6+).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement efficient and reusable frontend systems and libraries for future use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize web applications for maximum speed and scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough testing of frontend code to ensure high quality and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay updated on the latest trends and best practices in frontend development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in troubleshooting and debugging frontend issues as they arise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in code reviews to provide feedback and maintain code quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pursuing a degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of web fundamentals including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with frontend frameworks such as React, Vue.js, or Angular.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with version control systems, preferably Git.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of web performance optimization techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively in a team environment and communicate technical concepts clearly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for learning and staying updated on emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer For Interns:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Internship Duration: from 2 months or more&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Type of internship: &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;100% remote &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;or hybrid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt; in the office in Bremen (GER), Sofia (BG), Belgrade (SRB), Istanbul (TR), Sakarya (TR), Singapore (SGD)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0}&quot;&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Our mission&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;bub-content-body&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Constructor’s mission is to enable all educational organisations to provide high-quality digital education to 10x people with 10x efficiency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With strong expertise in machine intelligence and data science, Constructor’s all-in-one platform for education and research addresses today’s pressing educational challenges: access inequality, tech clutter, and low engagement of students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please send your resume in English only.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE CONSTRUCTOR GROUP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/&quot;&gt;Constructor Group&lt;/a&gt; is driven by the belief that knowledge is the solution to all evil. We are a global institution focused on making scientists, teachers, and students more effective and efficient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our integrated ecosystem focuses on fundamental technology needs relevant to science and education: generative AI, MetaPresence, computing, robotics, energy, health &amp;amp; bio, and neuroscience. &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/&quot;&gt;Constructor Group&lt;/a&gt; consists of three main pillars – &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.org/knowledge&quot;&gt;Constructor Knowledge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Constructor Capital&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://constructor.tech/?__hstc=100175169.8b0f85aa87aedb5f1cdd10e6c30d8a9b.1778592930857.1778592930857.1778592930857.1&amp;amp;__hssc=100175169.5.1778592430017&amp;amp;__hsfp=97c674a0edf8603ac2ef39b43750c9e0&quot;&gt;Constructor Tech&lt;/a&gt; – uniting science, technology, and education around a single deeply fundamental and yet very applied mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Constructor Group is looking for a Head of Engineering to lead the company’s technology and software development function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for defining and executing the technology strategy, managing engineering teams, ensuring high-quality product delivery, and building scalable, reliable, and secure technology solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a strong technical leader with a hands-on engineering background, experience managing development teams, and the ability to align technology decisions with business goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the software development function and manage engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the technology strategy in alignment with business and product goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the development roadmap together with product, business, and executive stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and high-quality delivery of software products and technical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable, secure, and reliable architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and improve engineering processes, development standards, code quality, and release management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage technical priorities, resource allocation, and delivery risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, mentor, and develop engineering managers, team leads, architects, and developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support recruitment, onboarding, and performance management for technical teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive best practices in software development, testing, DevOps, security, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and select technologies, tools, frameworks, and vendors when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate technical decisions, risks, and progress to senior leadership in a clear, business-oriented way.&lt;/li&gt;
&

