&lt;h4&gt;Internship Opportunity at the Research Unit of Constructor Technology in Partnership with the Observatory of Higher Education Innovations at Constructor University&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Overview:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Research Unit of Constructor Technology in Partnership with the Observatory of Higher Education Innovations at Constructor University is looking for a motivated student intern who is passionate about educational technologies and their applications. The ideal candidate is a second or third-year student with a strong interest in research, data analysis, and the EdTech industry. This internship offers valuable learning opportunities, mentorship, and hands-on experience in a dynamic field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in analyzing existing EdTech solutions, including platform and infrastructure software, as well as products aimed at end-users such as students, teachers, and administrative staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help investigate and assess the latest trends and innovations in the application of artificial intelligence in education.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team members and researchers to explore tools that enhance productivity and optimize routine tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively participate in a weekly work-group seminar where we discuss findings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the market analysis efforts, including studying economic indicators and trends to identify potential opportunities for the company&#39;s development in the EdTech sector.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in external EdTech and education-related activities and share insights with the entire team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Requirements:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled in a second or third year of a bachelor&#39;s program in information technology, economics, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of market research and data analysis, with coursework or projects in a related area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills, with the ability to work with information and learn to make informed decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills and the ability to work effectively within a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiasm for learning and contributing to the field of educational technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What Constructor Technology Offers:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A position in a leading company in the EdTech field, actively using innovations to transform education.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience and learning opportunities in market analysis and data-driven decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working hours with an expected duration of 6 months, with the possibility of extension based on performance and company needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
